                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Ketteler</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. von Holleben’s note of May 14, I
                    have the honor to inform you in accordance with instructions received that Mr.
                    Greiner, chancellor of the German consulate at Sydney, who has been
                    provisionally designated to act as the German member of the Samoan land
                    commission, has arrived at Apia, and that he entered upon the duties of the
                    office on the 1st of April of this year.</p>
                <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ketteler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
